{
  "texts": [
    "The study found that BERT-based models achieved results comparable to those of neural network models.",
    "However, the parallelization and pre-trained knowledge did not offer significant advantages over the CNN and RNN based models.",
    "Moreover, several other studies have reported similar results with BERT-based models (Rodriguez et al. 2019; Nadeem et al. 2019).",
    "On the contrary, Yang et al. (2020) demonstrated the utilization of BERT for improved performance results by extending its capabilities to predict both scores and ranks.",
    "Fine-tuning of BERT with multi-loss functions (Yang et al. 2020; Xie et al. 2022; Wang et al. 2022b) and augmenting BERT with essay-level features (Uto et al. 2020) have yielded results that surpass the state-of-the-art neural network methods in AES tasks."
  ]
}